                                         JOHANNESBURG - Limpopo police are searching for a group of armed robbers responsible for blowing up two ATMs at a petrol station in the Letsitele CBD near Tzaneen. It's understood the gang tied up the petrol attendants before blowing up the ATMs on Saturday night. Police say it's not yet known how much money the robbers fled with. The police's Moatshe Ngoepe said: “At this moment these suspects are still unknown and we’re therefore calling upon all members of the community who might assist us with information about these suspects to contact the nearest police station.”